48
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:48,000
FinOps is built on three phases.

49
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:54,000
Phase one is Inform. This is about visibility.
You cannot optimize what you cannot see.

50
00:04:54,000 --> 00:05:00,000
You cannot fix what you cannot measure.
You cannot save money on a service you don't know exists.

51
00:05:00,000 --> 00:05:06,000
So Phase one is all about getting data.
Tagging your resources so you know who owns what.

52
00:05:06,000 --> 00:05:12,000
Setting up Cost Explorer so you can query your spend.
Deploying Kubecost so you can see cost per namespace,
cost per pod, cost per team.

53
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:18,000
Knowing which team spent what on which service
in which region at which time of day.

54
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:24,000
Phase two is Optimize. This is about action.
Once you can see the waste, you need to eliminate it.

55
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:30,000
Rightsizing EC2 instances that are twice as big
as they need to be.

56
00:05:30,000 --> 00:05:36,000
Migrating gp2 volumes to gp3 for an instant 20% savings.
Buying Savings Plans for your stable workloads.

57
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:42,000
Running Karpenter to continuously consolidate your EKS nodes.
Actually reducing the number on the bill.

58
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:48,000
Phase three is Operate. This is about continuity.
Because here's the thing about cloud waste. It comes back.

59
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:54,000
You rightsize an instance today.
And three months later someone deploys a new service
and forgets to set resource limits.

60
00:05:54,000 --> 00:06:00,000
You add lifecycle policies to S3.
And next quarter someone creates a new bucket
and forgets to add the policy.

61
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:06,000
You tag everything. And a new intern spins up a test instance
with no tags.

62
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:12,000
So Phase three is about making sure the waste never comes back.
Budget alerts that email you when spend exceeds a threshold.

63
00:06:12,000 --> 00:06:18,000
AWS Config rules that flag untagged resources automatically.
Terraform guardrails that prevent non-compliant resources
from being created in the first place.

64
00:06:18,000 --> 00:06:24,000
IDP cost visibility that shows developers the impact of their deploy
before they click the button.

65
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:30,000
Most courses only teach Phase two.
They show you how to rightsize an instance and call it done.

66
00:06:30,000 --> 00:06:36,000
They give you a few commands, show you a few dashboards,
and send you on your way.

67
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:42,000
But without Phase one, you don't know what to rightsize.
You're just guessing.

68
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:48,000
You might rightsize the wrong instance.
You might miss the biggest cost driver entirely.

69
00:06:48,000 --> 00:06:54,000
You might save two hundred dollars
when you could have saved two thousand.

70
00:06:54,000 --> 00:07:00,000
And without Phase three, the waste creeps back in.
You do all this work, you feel great about yourself.

71
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:06,000
And then three months later you're right back where you started.
The bill is high again. The waste is back.

72
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:12,000
And you have to do the whole thing over.

