89
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:54,000
Here's why it's a revolution.

90
00:08:54,000 --> 00:09:00,000
Before Kubecost, you had to wait for the monthly AWS bill.
Then you had to download a CSV file with 47 columns of usage types
you didn't understand.

91
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:06,000
Then you had to manually map instance IDs to services.
Then you had to guess which team owned which resource.

92
00:09:06,000 --> 00:09:12,000
It took days. By the time you had answers,
the month was over and a new bill had arrived.

93
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:18,000
With Kubecost, when something changes in your cluster,
a new deployment, a scaled pod, a data transfer spike.

94
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:24,000
Kubecost creates a new cost allocation element in real time.
It then compares it to the historical baseline
to pinpoint the difference.

95
00:09:24,000 --> 00:09:30,000
And only the changed portion of your budget is flagged
for review.

